title: Germany: How to deregister a client in the Fiskaly webside.
text: Log in to Fiskaly an find the organization you want to make changes: On the organization side, go to SIGN DE V2 (Germany), find the client and press on the ID you want to change: Her you press the deregister button and confirm the deregistering with password 1234567890.
description:
Log in to Fiskaly an find the organization you want to make changes:


On the organization side, go to SIGN DE V2 (Germany), find the client and press on the ID you want to change:


Her you press the deregister button and confirm the deregistering with password 1234567890.

title: Austria: Read Certificate failed Karten Leser für lesen Certificate nicht gefunden
text: When performing a transaction on the POS and encountering the following error message, it’s most likely that the USB stick for the A-Trust card reader is not plugged into the PC.
description: When performing a transaction on the POS and encountering the following error message, it’s most likely that the USB stick for the A-Trust card reader is not plugged into the PC.

title: Germany: Transactions are not shown currectly on the Fiskaly homepage.
text: When the transactions for a certain clients are not loaded on the fiskaly homepage: it is mostly likely because there are too many transactions to be loaded. Comment from Fiskaly: "Due to the large number of transactions on the TSE or the client, querying the transactions is relatively complex." An easy work around is to querying transactions via the TSE by using the the following link: https://dashboard.fiskaly.com/da873923-c840-4721-b8fb-3a7e3d502f4a/kassensichv2/tss/ in this case: 2c24f498-7ad8-4a0b-ad9c-3f8a0e714a67 https://dashboard.fiskaly.com/da873923-c840-4721-b8fb-3a7e3d502f4a/kassensichv2/tss/2c24f498-7ad8-4a0b-ad9c-3f8a0e714a67
